* A server shop is a shop that is created with the /setshop command. It is a cuboid region defined by two points, p1 and p2. (These are set with the /setshop command.) It can only be created by admins with the hyperconomy.admin permission. A server shop is meant to be created by an administrator and then remain a permanent, unchanging shop that can not be changed by normal players.
* When entering a server shop, a customizable message (/setmessage command) will display. When exiting the shop, the shop exit message will display. (This can be disabled in config.yml)
* Multiple shops can be attached to the same economy, meaning if shop1 and shop2 are both in the "default" economy, selling 1 stone to shop1 will increase the stock of stone in shop2.
* Each server shop is a part of an economy which contains all of the items, stocks, and prices for the shop.
* A shop's economy can be changed manually be an admin by using the /setshopeconomy command. This will change all of the settings for all items in the shop.
* The settings and stocks of items in the shop can be viewed with the /objectsettings command.
